  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Food security, resilience and adaptation - REECALL</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to strengthen community resilience in disaster-prone rural and urban areas of Bangladesh under four thematic areas: disaster preparedness; gender equality and womens leadership; economic empowerment; and water, sanitation and hygiene. This current phase of the project focused on influencing decision-makers in government and the private sector from local to national levels, to ensure the rights of community members (relating to DRR, climate change, women, WASH, economic rights and access to social safety nets) in climate change affected areas are fulfilled.</narrative>
  </description>
